# Git workflow

After substantive edits (features, fixes, refactors that should be saved), **create a git commit** with a clear, conventional message (what changed and why in plain language). Use complete sentences in the body when helpful.

The **user pushes** to the remote themselves — do **not** run `git push` unless they explicitly ask you to push.
